wiki.summary: "I Had Some Help" is a song by Post Malone featuring country music singer Morgan Wallen. It was released as the lead single from Malone's upcoming sixth album through Republic and Mercury Records on May 10, 2024. "I Had Some Help" debuted atop the Billboard Hot 100 with the highest weekly sales and streams since 2020, marking Malone's sixth and Wallen's second #1 song. It has now become the second longest running #1 song of 2024, holding its position for four weeks in a row. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "I Had Some Help" is a song by Post Malone featuring country music singer Morgan Wallen. It was released as the lead single from Malone's upcoming sixth album through Republic and Mercury Records on May 10, 2024. "I Had Some Help" debuted atop the Billboard Hot 100 with the highest weekly sales and streams since 2020, marking Malone's sixth and Wallen's second #1 song. It has now become the second longest running #1 song of 2024, holding its position for four weeks in a row. The song has made history by debuting at #1 on both the Billboard Hot 100 and Billboard's Hot Country Songs chart, and maintaining the top spot on each for its first four weeks, a feat never achieved before. The song debuted at #1 on the 2024 Billboard's Annual Songs of the Summer chart and concurrently tops the chart for a second week. It also debuted atop on the Billboard Global 200 chart and peaked at #1 on the charts in Australia, Canada, Ireland and Norway. Read more on Last.fm.
